style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>To change any attribute of a ship or base simply
double-click it. This will display an editing panel at the right of the scr=
een.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Here you can edit the=
 name of
the ship or base, change which empire it belongs to, and alter the amount of
fuel it carries.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>If the ship is a mili=
tary
ship you can assign it to a fleet. You can also control whether the ship or
base is automated.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>If the ship or base h=
as troop
storage components you can add or remove troops. You cannot add more troops
than the ship or base has room to store.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Note that you cannot =
add
troops to ships or bases of pirate factions or ships and bases that are
independent (have no empire).</span></p>

